Third-party origins and adaptations
===================================

Etch (MIT)
----------
The Hugo templates in `layouts/` and the stylesheets in `assets/css/` are
derived from the Etch theme by Lukas Joswiak:

  https://github.com/LukasJoswiak/etch
  commit b304186c260f574d281a495f5ceb4d8ac382cbe5

Etch is used as a starter, not as a theme dependency: the needed templates and
CSS were copied into this repository and are maintained here. License text:
`LICENSES/Etch.txt`.

Local adaptations of the Etch-derived layer:

- templates renamed/restructured for the current Hugo template system
  (post-0.146 lookup names, `layouts/_partials/`);
- text column widened to about 70ch;
- more prominent article title and larger section spacing;
- blockquotes are not italicized;
- inline-code styling; code blocks scroll horizontally;
- visible focus styles;
- page-specific description, canonical, Open Graph and Twitter Card metadata;
- RSS autodiscovery for the posts feed and per-tag term feeds; the built-in
  Hugo RSS template is used instead of Etch's `rss.xml`;
- auto dark mode kept, the `dark = "on"/"off"` config switch dropped;
- build-time math rendering (Goldmark passthrough + `transform.ToMath`).

Fonts (SIL OFL 1.1)
-------------------
`static/vendor/fonts/` contains self-hosted webfonts, served from this site
with no third-party requests:

- Inter 4.1 (variable, normal + italic) by Rasmus Andersson,
  https://github.com/rsms/inter — license: `LICENSES/Inter.txt`;
- JetBrains Mono 2.304 (regular + bold) by JetBrains,
  https://github.com/JetBrains/JetBrainsMono — license:
  `LICENSES/JetBrainsMono.txt`.

KaTeX (MIT)
-----------
`static/vendor/katex/` contains the KaTeX 0.16.21 stylesheet and fonts, used
for build-time math rendering (no KaTeX JavaScript is shipped). License text:
`LICENSES/KaTeX.txt`. The version matches the KaTeX version embedded in the
Hugo release pinned in `.hugo-version` (`internal/warpc/js/package.json` at
the Hugo tag). Only the `.woff2` fonts are vendored; the `.woff`/`.ttf`
fallbacks referenced by `katex.min.css` are intentionally omitted, so font
requests from very old browsers will 404.
